<HEADLINE>
FT  18 MAY 93 / Parliament and Politics: Court services switch considered
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MR John Taylor, spokesman in the Commons for Lord Mackay, the Lord
Chancellor, confirmed yesterday that consideration was being given to
switching responsibility for the provision of court services away from the
public sector.
He said the initial use of an agency under the so-called 'next steps'
arrangements was being deliberated upon with very great care.
Mr Paul Boateng, a Labour front bench spokesman, underlined the concern
aroused by the 'disastrous impact of privatisation on other aspects of the
justice system'.
He called for an assurance that the best interests of the consumers of legal
services were properly safeguarded.
Mr Taylor agreed that 'it is the consumers and users whose interests must be
considered the most important'.
</TEXT>
