<TEXT>
PERUVIANS struggled to work yesterday as many public transport drivers
stayed off the streets in an 'armed strike' called by Maoist Shining Path
rebels to mark the 13th anniversary of the start of their war on the state,
AP reports from Lima.
The rebels stepped up their campaign of violence in advance of the strike.
