<HEADLINE>
FT  17 MAY 93 / UK Company News: Break for the Border placing
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
BREAK FOR the Border Group, whose business is that of restaurateur, live
music venue and nightclub from two sites in the West End, is offering 4.81m
shares in a placing at 48p.
That values the whole of the company at Pounds 4.73m. A listing will be
sought and dealings are expected to start on Wednesday.
Fiske &amp; Co is organising the placing which will raise Pounds 1.67m for the
company. Of that Pounds 547,000 will repay shareholders' loans and Pounds
328,000 bank indebtedness; the balance will finance expansion and working
capital requirements.
Break for the Border cafes have been established as Western style saloon
bars and restaurants with live rock music. The food available is Tex-Mex, a
mixture of Texan and Mexican dishes.
The company's eventual goal is the operation of units using the Break for
the Border and Borderline theme in a number of principal cities across the
world.
Negotiations are in hand for an opening in New York, giving new musical acts
the chance to play in a top city venue where they can be seen by promoters
and record company executives, as well as the public.
In the year ended March 31 1993 turnover came to Pounds 4.1m (Pounds 4m) and
operating profit to Pounds 566,000 (Pounds 470,000, giving a margin up from
11.7 to 13.8 per cent. The pre-tax outcome worked through at Pounds 477,000
(Pounds 261,000).
The placing comprises the issue of 4.1m shares by the company and the sale
of 706,000 by existing shareholders.
</TEXT>
