FT  17 MAY 93 / Letter: What's best for the Saudis?
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr GHAZI ALGOSAIBI
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, We have often been told that the last thing Saudi Arabia wants to see
on its doorstep is a dictatorial regime in Baghdad. We have also often been
told that the last thing Saudi Arabia wants is a fundamentalist regime in
Tehran.
Now, Eric Watkins ('Success of Yemeni elections prompts worries for Saudis',
May 14) quotes, approvingly, a western diplomat who asserts 'the last thing
Saudi royalty wants on its doorstep is a successful little democracy in
Yemen'.
Will somebody, please, tell us what is it exactly that we want on our
doorstep?
Ghazi Algosaibi,
ambassador,
Royal Embassy of Saudi Arabia,
London
