<HEADLINE>
FT  17 MAY 93 / Assisted areas map ready for EC
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE GOVERNMENT is expected this week to submit to the European Commission
its redrawn assisted areas map, the subject of intensive lobbying by the
regions.
The map will specify areas in which companies can qualify for UK government
and EC regional aid.
It is expected to provoke fierce controversy by including areas of inner
London and south-east England, at the expense of parts of Wales, the
Midlands and the north of England.
</TEXT>
