<TEXT>
DISCOUNT retailing will remain the fastest growing sector of UK retailing
even when the recession is over, according to a report by Verdict, the
retail research company, Neil Buckley writes.
Verdict says discounting will be a significant force in food retailing and
clothing and general-purpose stores. Experience in the US and Germany
suggests the UK is ripe for expansion.
In addition to growing price sensitivity among consumers, Verdict says the
demand for price-led retailing is underpinned by the massive expansion in
retail floorspace in the 1980s, which has left excess capacity in the 1990s.
